<p>heavily reinforced and we were compelled to retire back to the summit again.</p>
<p>We then commenced to dig in. For 2 days we dug with our entrenching tools. Every chance we got between the mad rushes of the Turks we dug for our lives. By about the 28th our position was secure and we had nearly conected up our whole front. On the 29.4.15 we were relieved by a Naval Brigade and 2 Battalions of R.M.L.Is. We commenced to reform</p>
